Minor suggestion: maybe add the following:
```scala
private implicit class ProcessOs(val process: Process) extends AnyVal {
  def block(): Unit = assert(proc.waitFor(5, TimeUnit.SECONDS), "Process took more than 5 seconds to exit")
}
```
then you could replace all of the calls to `proc.waitFor` with `proc.block()`. It also allows the time duration to be easily changed in one place. None of the these tests should take more than a few hundred milliseconds so I think 5 seconds is plenty of time to wait.

